<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<article desc="SVG shapes support">
   <meta desc="This article presents the support for SVG shapes" />
   This article presents the support for SVG shapes<note>See <a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/SVG11/shapes.html">Basic Shapes</a></note>.
   
   <title title="attributes supported for all elements" />
   All elements support the following attributes:
   <ul>
      <li>
         The <code>id</code> attribute</li>           
      <li>
         The attributes for <ref id="svg transform support" />
      </li>           
      <li>
         The attributes for <ref id="svg styling support" />
      </li> 
      <li>
         The attributes for <ref id="clipPath support" />
      </li>             
   </ul>
      
   <title title="g" />
   No attributes are supported besides those supported for all elements. 
   
   <title title="rect" />
   The following attributes are supported:
   <ul>
      <li>
         <code>x</code>
      </li>
      <li>
         <code>y</code>
      </li>        
      <li>
         <code>width</code>
      </li>
      <li>
         <code>height</code>
      </li>  
      <li>
         <code>rx</code>
      </li>
      <li>
         <code>ry</code>
      </li>     
      <li>
         <code>color</code>
      </li>     
      <li>
         <code>fill-color</code>
      </li>      
      <li>
         <code>opacity</code>
      </li>   
      <li>
         <code>fill-opacity</code>
      </li>    
      <li>
         The attributes for <ref id="Strokes support" />
      </li>               
   </ul>
   
   <title title="line" />
   The following attributes are supported:
   <ul>
      <li>
         <code>x1</code>
      </li>
      <li>
         <code>y1</code>
      </li>        
      <li>
         <code>x2</code>
      </li>
      <li>
         <code>y2</code>
      </li>       
      <li>
         <code>stroke</code>
      </li>        
      <li>
         <code>opacity</code>
      </li>     
      <li>
         The attributes for <ref id="Strokes support" />
      </li>                 
   </ul>   
   
